Dialogs.Dialog: Yes, next I'll serve and volley at you.
Hey, have you hear？ Rumors about our coach, Suzuki-sensei！
Ah, Miyoshi. A rumor？ Do you know anything about it ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
No, I don't know... Hey, the serve and volley manager――
Really, seriously！ The guy in my class heard he was called in...
What was its name again？ Was it "Masami-san"？
That's it！ I heard he's obsessed with Masami-san.
Hey, isn't that... an affair？ No way！？
I don't think it's Suzuki-sensei either...
What's going on today... Is it possible to work here？ Let's go for today.
Our club is just messy... right？
Hmm？ It's weird to hear you sigh like that, are you okay, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
I get along with everyone in the tennis club, but... I don't really like to play games. I've thinking...
Certainly. Is the current atmosphere too loose there？
At first I thought they joined because they wanted to play tennis. Practice, sweat and improve...
I can really feel that I am improving myself, so I try hard at sports...
Well, not everyone takes it seriously...
So, why don't you make a suggestion？ Shall we practice hard for the manager and everyone？
Huh？ Emm, that's... No, that's okay.
I want to keep everyone as they are, and I was just saying those things.
Okay, then next make pairs for boys and girls.
Are you looking for a fight... Huh, Takane-chan！
Naruto-kun. Ah it's nice. You decided to pair up, ▲主人公＊▲.
Well, you get used to it.
That's right. Even you, Takane-chan is always with Miyoshi, right？ My girl database is up to date.
Hehe, not today. Miyoshi-chan is on her vacation, so I think I have to pick someone――
Well then, I'm going to run around！
Komaki？ Ah yes, she recently joined the club...
Hello！ I'm a freshman, my name is Komaki Mina！ Um...
Takane-senpai, can you run with me as well？ For the pairing with a senpai.
Yes, of course. I would like that. Let's get along, okay？
Because I've been longing to work with you for a long time, Takane-senpai！
You're the ace of the girls' club, your grades are in the top and, as a bonus, you come from a family of doctors――
Yes. I... I want to play tennis with Takane-senpai. So please play with me.
Yes, I understand. Let's play tennis together.
Then, are you going now？ Give your best, both of you！
My senpai told me to play tennis with her, so today is Komaki's tennis anniversary！
Uh, yes？ Want to go a little further？
First grade, Komaki Mina. She looks like a handful, but she might be not bad？
(First grade, Komaki... Will you be okay ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
Hehe, Komaki-san, she's been like this since we left the locker room. Right？
Don't be embarrassed you two. Komaki heard about it, okay？ You're the lovey dovey couple certified by the tennis club.
"What is the nature of your relationship？" is one of the mysteries of Towano. But, she chose you, so don't worry BF-senpai！
Well, it's fine... I'm sorry but can we train in the back, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes. I'm not good at the low courses, so let's do it.
I'm still a beginner, and far from being good enough, I still need more practice.
I see... I'll help you out. Do you want me to give you a hand？
Takane-senpai... Now all boys will be crazy for you, just like me...
Geez, what a strange girl. Let's go train.
I'm sorry. See you later, okay？
Boyfriend-senpai, I'm sorry, but I'm borrowing Takane-senpai.
I was just calling you. Teehee▼
Hehe！ Geez, what a strange girl！
Well then, that's all for today. Good work.
Good work... Maybe I'm not that tired, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Is this another story about girls？
It seems that a new couch will come to our club next time, right？
A coach？ I don't think it's from a strong school.
Suzuki-sensei has no tennis experience, most of our training go to the manager. The principal was angry when he found out.
If I was the manager... I wouldn't want everyone to hate me.
Right？ So, there's a coach who can teach tennis properly. He won the All Japan Tourney, and taught overseas pros.
That's amazing. I wonder why's he coming here.
He knows the principal. He seems to have returned to Japan, and he will teach just for a time.
Aren't you happy？ You don't want to practice hard？
Heh. The new coach is a young, beautiful girl, so it's already decided！
In my intuition, the coach is the rumored "Masami-san". I'm looking forward to it♪
Everyone gather around... *Yawn* Okay, let's start...
Our manager seems more sleepy than usual...
Actually, yesterday I was playing with Yoshida of the soccer club until morning... I didn't sleep much...
(Certainly, he seems to be a lazy person.)
Alright, it’s a bit early, but today’s practice――
I'm saying it's not over yet. Club activity is not over yet.
...What？ I don't know who you are, but if you're an outsider, you should be a sensei――
Today I was appointed as the coach of this club. I am Masami Oiwa.
An amazing person just came ▲高嶺＊＊▲...
Truly... a trained body, a serve that seems to have the power of 200 kg. Surely a world class top player...
That's right. You have good eyes...
Is this the court？ I can practice well with this... I see.
You there. Both of you, come here.
Let me introduce myself. I'm a tennis member at Tonarino High School, where I used to coach.
I knew it... Tonarino's tennis club is a prestigious inter-high regular, and it has won over 10 years...
I'm Yukari Chono, a second year tennis player Ace at Tonarino High School.
It's Osamu Kuroki, second year and supposed ace of the men's club.
Why are so many people of Tonarino High School...
From now on, boys will play with Kuroki and girls will play with Chono, one game at a time.
If you don't want to obey, you can leave this place.
What's up, don't hesitate. Nobody will quit？... Then, let's start the matches.
(A match with Tonarino inter-high regular. Will they be our opponents？)
Only three or four people can barely play tennis...
(You were the only one able to pass your match ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Coach Oiwa. Do we still have to be here？
That's right. Can I go home？
Takane Manaka... Yes！ You were at a junior club in elementary school, right？ Do you remember？
It was fun today. I'll see you at the court next time, okay？ See ya.
I understand your ability now. Now then, run 10 laps around.
Coach Oiwa is really an amazing person.
Huh？ It seems like you're having fun...
It's been a while since I met Chono-san, she's really good and her hits are like a boy's...
I wonder if Coach Oiwa is capable of making such things...
I'll try my best to follow Coach Oiwa. I'm sure tennis will be more fun. I'm sure everyone will...
I see. I will do it too.
I want to like tennis as much as you do, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
(Alright, I'll get excited to play tennis！)
From today, we will do this my way.
But, we have a practice menu――
It feels like this club has been hijacked.
I'll explain the menu. Gather around.
Unreasonable... I can't do it anymore... Where's the practice... I'm just running...
Komaki-san, just a little more. Give it your all！
We're holding a meeting. Gather around.
Next time, we will play a match against Tonarino.
I will get to play with Chono-san again...
If you can't do one set there, you should quit.
Quit... It's impossible for us to do one set against them...
I see. If you know the results, do you want to quit already？
Hmm... nice eyes. Don't forget those eyes.
Schedule will be announced as soon as it is decided. That's all.
Quitting the club... Do you think the Coach was serious？
No way... I'm sure he said that to make us take this seriously.
He's a tough person, but I don't think he's doing something unreasonable.
I have to do my best.
If you give up that fast, you will be left behind.
(Hah. Stroke and Volley, 10 more sets after changing courses...)
You there！ You footing is shallow！
No！ Wait more for the ball！
Stay right there！ Do not move！
It's just a crunch; warm and massage, you'll be okay...
...It's fine, your calf will be fine.
Alright！ The rest, continue with the practice！
I'm fine. I got a massage and it healed. He's an amazing coach, isn't he？
I also have a licence for sports massages. Next time, ask me to heal you, okay？
The person whose name is said now, will get on the court. The others, run 30 laps around the courts.
Don't use your wrist, one more time！
Slow！ Do not react after seeing the ball！
Don't go out with that kind of practice, Takane...
What's wrong, get in the court.
Hey, what's your take on Coach Oiwa.
I can't keep up with this.
We aren't playing tennis？ Most of us are out the court today？ Right？
Yes. The only ball I used was the one I picked from the grounds. Our manager and Takane are still fine.
That's not true. The we are directly hit by the coach！
You haven't you changed your clothes yet ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes. Just wanted to practice a little more.
When the Coach pointed some things, I thought I would repeat them.
I think my endurance has improved a lot thanks to running, and it's fun...
Yes... it's hard... but it's fun. I feel I like playing sports is fun.
Takane-senpai, it's me Komaki, can I bother you for a minute？
I was bad, so I couldn't keep up at all during club activities... but when I did a serve！ It's fun... Hehehe！
Yes... I get it, should we do it together？
She seems to be having fun during practice. She is different from us.
So you say, what about Komaki-san？
(Alright, we will make this happen, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Komaki-san, you seem to be getting tired, so maybe we should round up.
Hah, Hah, no. I'm still doing fine.
I don't want to be the cause of Takane-senpai's lack of practice...
Komaki will forget about her tiredness！
Geez. But it's getting late, should we leave it here？ We can do it next time.
Yes, it looked like you were having fun. I should have joined.
Boyfriend-senpai, don't you think it would be unfair to partner with someone else other than Takane-senpai？
Unfair？ Well, that's what it is.
Hehe. C'mon, let's go. If you keep sweating, you will catch a cold.
You've been recently close to Komaki these days, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Yes, it's fun to be with her.
Being a beginner who came in the middle, I'm sure it will be difficult, but she's hanging in there.
Yes. She's cute, single- minded and dedicated... Hehe.
Hehe, no... Geez, if you imagine it, it's cute. Hehehe.
Today's practice will be in groups.
Group A focuses in game format, group B manly performs basic training.
(We're finally done, it was really tough today...)
I'm tired... I'm sorry, but can you continue with court maintenance.
Hah, what do you mean？ I'm tired too.
It's okay, you were only doing the basics. You can't tired.
What do you mean, group A seems like isn't tired enough.
Let's have a duel now. Group B against Group A！
Hey, hey, why don't we all practice together after the club is over？
Sure. Then, after this, let's go to Winning Burger？ It's been too long！
I still want to practice. I don't want to fall behind Group B...
I can't help it. I've been practicing hard and getting better... I want to play tennis properly！
The atmosphere inside the tennis club is getting weird...
I wish it would return to normal soon.
Everyone started to work hard and grow stronger.
Of course, fights are not good. When it comes to strength, it's natural for competition to start.
Do you think the current tennis club is better, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
No, not like that... If you continue doing this and get results, everyone can make up.
Besides, I'm sure that you will be able to understand the emotions you couldn't before.
I think going backwards it's no good...
(You are getting a little moody these days, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
I want to see you whole body. Turn around.
I see... It's a good way to build muscles...
What you're wearing is nice. It suits you.
Did the Coach just praised you？ Amazing！ He doesn't praise any of the other members.
Alright, I ran 10 km around！！ My body is getting used to it！
Hah, Hah... We run around every day！
Emm？ The girl of the 5km？ Didn't she finish not to long ago？
What is are doing, you should start practice when you finish your laps.
Komaki, you will run laps around until the end of the day.
Takane, do what you need to do. Now, group A, practice！
(Isn't this what you really wanted for the tennis club, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
(I wonder if Komaki's late again... ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
Next. Group A, go to the court. Group B, divide into 2 groups, swinging and picking up balls. Start！
Alright. That's it for today. Dismissed.
Komaki. Don't you feel like quitting yet？
I will understand it. You don't have to be in the club any more. You don't have to come anymore.
Please, let me stay in the tennis club！ All I have to do is do 10 laps and do 10 sets！
Do it then. I'm not convinced enough.
I wonder if Komaki-san is doing okay...
With what the Coach said to her...
He didn't had to say it so bluntly.
Only running and picking up balls... I wish she could play tennis.
I wonder if I can do anything to help...
(I made a mistake... I made a mistake looking at the clock and came an hour earlier...)
Well, sometimes that happens. Why did you do it？
I woke up early, so I thought about doing some morning workout.
In the morning...？ Well then, I'll tag along.
Ah, Takane-senpai！ And, boyfriend-senpai！ It's getting hot this morning！
Komaki, what are you doing here...？
Actually, I've been doing it since joining... I thought I might not be good, and I'm embarrassed.
Hey, if you'd like, why don't we practice together today？
I think if we do it together we will get better. Let's do our best to be recognized by the Coach, okay？
Aren't you getting tired this morning？
Okay, do your best with club activities！
Try to focus on the soleus muscle.
Hey, we will have our duel today.
Don't think you're gonna win if you run away！
It's not that, don't give us strange things to do！
Hey you, don't forget about your duel with me！
(She's late... What are you doing ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
It just seems like I can't get nothing right...
No, everyone is motivated. I have to practice more and more to become stronger！
Even so, it looks hard... Isn't it hard on your body？
Nothing like that, I will be fine.
(You don't seem to enjoy tennis like this, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
(Now then, let's start early in the morning！)
Somehow, I'm sorry to make you come here so early. For Komaki to do something like this...
Geez, what are you talking about. Here, do your best！
So... for the time being, what is Komaki's training menu？
I think it's best to practice in the court... But, first I think it's better to focus on one thing each time.
I want to achieve results as soon as possible so that Coach can recognize her...
Umm... What do you want to learn？ Komaki？
Um, the return serve... Komaki wants to learn Takane-senpai's return serve！
Return, huh... Yes, I understand. Then once we do serve, shall we do a special training for returns？
Hah... Homeroom is about to start. Should we stop for today？
Oh no... I have to take a shower, let's hurry！
Yes, can we continue after club activities, right？
Hey, it's still early but you barely can see the balls now. Should we head back home now？
Yes. Komaki-san, should we also go home？
Komaki？ How are you feeling about your special training？
It's completely different from training alone！ I'm having fun for the first time！
Hehe. Komaki-san, aren't you always playing tennis happily？
This is part of Komaki's youth！
Yes... I really wanted to join the tennis club, and I was late compared to my friends, but I did it.
Buy, why did you chose tennis？
For a while, after entering school, I didn't feel like I fit with the rest of my class...
Ah, I was not bullied！ I know everyone tried to get along.
So me, Komaki, can't go back to that...
I'm bad with speaking my mind, and always idle...
Therefore, after lunch or after school, there was no place to go and I wandered around the schoolyard...
And then, I saw her. I saw Takane-senpai at the tennis court.
She was really cool, beautiful... her serves, her returns... It rallied me.
This isn't like catchball, right？ It's a little different, and if I could be like you, I could get along with everyone.
Because everyone seems to be having fun, and when I saw it I thought "Oh, this is my youth, I'd like to be here！"
Ehehe... That's why I want to learn！ If it was Takane's serve, it would be great！
Yes... Well then, shall we do another special training？ It's tougher than Coach Oiwa's, is that okay？
(You laughed. I haven't seen you like this in a long time ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
I wonder if it was strange...
Strange about what... Ah, do you mean tennis？
I was thinking about what Komaki-san said.
I wonder if I was the one who Komaki-san admired...
I'm sure she's mistook me for someone else.
No matter how strong you get, you must have fun... I should play tennis because it's fun.
(Yes, tennis must be fun to do...)
Take a break, be sure to rehydrate.
Hey, you used the court yesterday during breaktime！
It's fine, first come first served！
It's just we have to use the court―― Kyaa！
Geez, why is a ball here...？
Sorry！ I haven't picked it up yet...
No, I'll pick it up now.
Everyone, you've improved a lot lately.
Yes. You've been getting a lot of practice. It's amazing！
Komaki-san, I'll help you pick up the balls.
There's no need to do that！ Takane-senpai is the female Ace！
But, if we do it together it'll be faster... We can do this during our break, right？
That makes me happy, but it's...
Then I'll help you. That's fine, right？
Hehe！ The three of us together. Okay？
It about time to go play against Tonarino.
(Finally, the day of our match comes.)
It's finally our match against Tonarino, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Do you think we can do it？
I don't know if losing really means we have to quit...
I want to do my best until the very end.
I want to play tennis in a club with everyone.
Let's do our best in the matches！
(Today is our match against Tonarino High School...)
We have no choice, but to do it.
(So this is Tonarino High... this is a great tennis court.)
Chono-san. I'm looking forward for today.
Same here. I'm looking forward to it.
Get started right away. Get ready.
This should be all the members. Kuroki is going against boys and Chono is going against girls.
Until everybody loses, Towano wins if they get even one set.
The only point we could get was yours ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Chono, don't play lukewarm against your opponents. From here on, win with service ace and return ace.
If you can't do it against Towano, you can't win at Inter-High.
Kuroki. I don't think you have any trouble. I wonder if you've been skipping since I left.
Damn it, don't just say whatever you want.
Don't give up yet, do your best until the end！
Don't let it go to waste！
I see, they're going to take this seriously...
What does that mean if they have to quit the team？
If they all lose, Towano High School Tennis Club will be disbanded.
It doesn't matter to you, I'm not going to teach those who can't win.
That was an impressive home run. To make that kind of mistake...
Chono, go back. Spare player... Go.
I wonder about that. The Coach will call you an idiot.
No way, really？ Is that really Kuroki, the service Ace！？
He's doing the same as Chono-san.
Towano High School... Their technique is lacking, but everyone seems to have fun... Compared to us...
And that would be a waste to let go...
Sports are competitions. In competitions, victory is everything.
It seems like I'm the last one...
Manager, we leave it to you！
He's getting really tired... Manager, give it your all！
It's just a flesh wound, Tezuka. It can be cured by taping and massaging, but you cannot continue.
The last member we have: Komaki-san！
Komaki is not a tennis club member.
She's a good tennis member, and it's weird not to be in the match！
Yes, no matter what the Coach says, Komaki is a member of Towano's Tennis Club.
So, what if I said anyone could chose their favorites. You might win. However, if Komaki is there, you'll lose.
That's what means to win in a competition.
...Takane-senpai, please. I can't do it. I don't want to cause our disbanding...
Even if the result is bad, if everyone gives their all, we can be in our tennis club until the end, right？
Coach, we will change our manager. The points will stay as they are.
Do whatever you want... Komaki, go into the court. It will resume at 15-30.
It's not looking good... Even though Komaki is giving her all...
But if it hadn't been for that special training, it might all have been a no-touch ace.
If she keeps doing it, she might have a chance...
You're right... Do your best！ Komaki！
Shut up. With this... I will it end all！
I did it. I returned it...
It looks like she's won, though she hasn't won yet.
But it looks like she's having fun... I think it's better than us when we won the tournament.
A little more, don't give up！
I'm sorry, I ended up getting only 1 point... I lost.
But the results of our special training came out, right？ I'm very happy！
...Is it time for us to disband？
Winning is not all, it's about how you play tennis. Right？
Today you're dismissed. Get ready for tomorrow's practice.
For tomorrow... Does this means we won't be disbanded！
If you want to continue playing tennis, you have to do it by yourselves.
Yes, the tennis club will continue！
I'm glad the tennis club didn't had to be disbanded.
I noticed something when I was watching Komaki-san.
Komaki-san was like me before I met you. Looking at everyone in the club from a lonely place...
Therefore, I intended to help Komaki-san, but while I was doing it, I realized I was the one learning.
No matter how hard you try... It's meaningless if you don't have friends to share joy.
I think Komaki is similar to you too, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
I realized it when I saw you. I'm the same as her, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
I realized... that I like the hard-working and pure you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
I also like you... You always look at me kindly...
Hey, nobody seems to be watching now, ▲主人公＊▲...
Takane-senpai！ Boyfriend-senpai！ I'm sorry to interrupt your lovey-dovey display！
It's terrible, the Coach is gone！
Is it true you are going？
It was a promise, the day has come and I'm leaving, that's it.
Play tennis the way you want to. I don't like it, but... it doesn't have to be liked by anyone.
I wanted to see your growth a little more...
No, don't worry about it, it's nothing.
You're too close！ I don't have that kind of hobby！
(Thank you Coach. It was fun to play tennis with you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
